{"_id":"D3BZaCzUMQcWgUeF","name":"Hallowed by the Meal","type":"feat","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/sin-eater.png","data":{"description":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Special Elite','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: white; mso-themecolor: background1; background: black; mso-highlight: black;\">At the beginning of each adventure after eating a human or evil spirit, the digested fate, virtues and sins grants you a power equal to either a random clean or unclean scroll -once-. No need to roll to use it.</span></p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EI4zbOlxQspAyGze":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7T75J3NMsouZyU3Q"}}}
{"_id":"GhuFnPrfEgzS0NjU","name":"Sin Eater","type":"class","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/sin-eater.png","data":{"abilities":"<p>Horrid, greasy, pockmarked, and sickly looking: roll 3d6-2 for presence.</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Special Elite','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: white; mso-themecolor: background1; background: black; mso-highlight: black;\">Malformed in Limb &amp; Body: you may only wear Tier 1 Armor and may never wield zweih&auml;nder or battle axes.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Special Elite','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: white; mso-themecolor: background1; background: black; mso-highlight: black;\">Eater of the Dead: may eat -any- organic matter without getting sick, no matter how foul.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Special Elite','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: white; mso-themecolor: background1; background: black; mso-highlight: black;\">Twisted Wretches: you begin the game with one specialty, and may roll for another the first time the character gets better. May re-roll one or both when getting better later on.</span></p>","armorTableDie":"1d1","description":"THE DEAD ARE CORRUPT. THE STOMACHS OF SIN EATERS PURIFY THEIR ROTTING FLESH.\nThe ghastly life of the poor sods who end up devouring the dead is never chosen, rather it is often a form of punishment handed down by fate.\nTheologians have debated about the qualities of these unfortunate souls who seem to be holiness garbed in disgusting wretchedness. Are they malign being warped by arcane chaos, do they belong to a cursed bloodline, or are they touched by some cruel god? Many believe that their souls are eternally damned as the cost for forgiving those they eat. When a sin-eater dies, their bodies are salted and burned. Their remains are not allowed to be buried in the hallowed ground of most cemeteries.\nThe two-headed basilisks of the one true faith abhor them. But from the lowest peasant to the grandest king, many call for them near the final end, so that they might find peace in the hereafter.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"2d6","startingItems":"morkborg-3p.class-sin-eater,Malformed in Limb and Body\nmorkborg-3p.class-sin-eater,Eater of the Dead","startingPresence":"3d6-2","startingRolls":"morkborg-3p.rolls-sin-eater,Most of your life you were,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-sin-eater,Twisted Wretches,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d1"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EI4zbOlxQspAyGze":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KRuRArsbsnW4laVQ"}}}
{"_id":"Q1rqoynHuh57HPvy","name":"Horrible Teeth","type":"weapon","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/sin-eater.png","data":{"containerSpace":0,"description":"<p><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Special Elite','serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: white; mso-themecolor: background1; background: black; mso-highlight: black;\">You file and sharpen your ever-growing teeth, which grants you a savage bite. DR:10 to attack, deals d6 damage. Must be close to the target. 1-2 on a d6 that the enemy gets a free attack.</span></p>","carryWeight":0,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d6","handed":"1","weaponType":"melee"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"EI4zbOlxQspAyGze":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mAUVgG4ms8XCnzPQ"}}}
